---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Chinese Cuisine" description="Explore the diverse and delicious world of Chinese cuisine - from Sichuan's fire to Cantonese subtlety">
  
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative h-[70vh] flex items-center overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1555126634-323283e090fa?w=1920&q=80"
        alt="Chinese food spread"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#1a1a1a]/95 to-[#C41E3A]/60"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#D4AF37] mb-4">CUISINE</span>
        <h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl text-white mb-6">Chinese Cuisine</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-stone-300 leading-relaxed">
          Eight great regional cuisines, ancient tea ceremonies, and a philosophy of food that spans 5,000 years.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#FFFEF7]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#C41E3A] mb-4">PHILOSOPHY</span>
          <h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-[#1a1a1a] mb-6">More Than Sustenance</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 mb-6">
            In Chinese culture, food is never just food. It's medicine, social glue, ritual, and art form all at once. The concept of "yi shi wei" (以食为天) — "regard food as heaven" — reflects how central eating is to Chinese civilization.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 mb-6">
            The balance of yin and yang extends to the kitchen: cooling foods for summer, warming foods for winter. The five flavors — sweet, sour, bitter, pungent, salty — must dance in harmony on every plate.
          </p>
          <div class="p-6 bg-[#C41E3A]/5 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-[#C41E3A]">
            <p class="font-display text-xl italic text-[#1a1a1a]">
              "Food is the first necessity of the people."
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mt-2">— Ancient Chinese Proverb</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563245372-f21724e3856d?w=800&q=80"
            alt="Traditional dim sum"
            class="rounded-xl shadow-2xl"
          />
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -left-6 bg-[#1a1a1a] text-white p-6 rounded-lg">
            <div class="stat-number text-3xl mb-1">8</div>
            <div class="text-sm tracking-wide">Great Cuisines</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Eight Cuisines -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#1a1a1a]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#D4AF37] mb-4">REGIONAL DIVERSITY</span>
        <h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-white mb-4">The Eight Great Cuisines</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Each region of China has developed its own distinct culinary identity, shaped by climate, resources, and centuries of tradition.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        {[
          { name: 'Sichuan', emoji: '🌶️', desc: 'Bold, spicy, and numbing. Famous for Mapo Tofu and Kung Pao Chicken.', color: 'bg-red-600' },
          { name: 'Cantonese', emoji: '🥢', desc: 'Delicate flavors, fresh ingredients. Dim sum, har gow, char siu.', color: 'bg-amber-500' },
          { name: 'Shandong', emoji: '🌊', desc: 'Seafood-focused, crispy textures. Original home of Peking Duck.', color: 'bg-cyan-600' },
          { name: 'Jiangsu', emoji: '🏯', desc: 'Light, fresh, slightly sweet. Precise knife techniques.', color: 'bg-emerald-600' },
          { name: 'Zhejiang', emoji: '🌸', desc: 'Soft, tender, delicate. Famous for Dongpo Pork.', color: 'bg-pink-500' },
          { name: 'Fujian', emoji: '🗻', desc: 'Umami-rich, seafood soups. Buddha Jumps Over the Wall.', color: 'bg-teal-600' },
          { name: 'Hunan', emoji: '🔥', desc: 'Pungent and hot. Smoked and cured meats, chili in everything.', color: 'bg-orange-600' },
          { name: 'Anhui', emoji: '⛰️', desc: 'Wild herbs, simple preparations. Chefs cook with torch oil.', color: 'bg-green-700' }
        ].map(cuisine => (
          <div class="bg-stone-800 rounded-xl p-6 hover:bg-stone-700 transition-colors">
            <div class={`w-12 h-12 rounded-full ${cuisine.color} flex items-center justify-center text-2xl mb-4`}>
              {cuisine.emoji}
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-white mb-2">{cuisine.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm">{cuisine.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tea Culture -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#FFFEF7]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1544787219-7f47ccb76574?w=800&q=80"
            alt="Chinese tea ceremony"
            class="rounded-xl shadow-2xl"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
          <span class="inline-block font-heading text-sm tracking-[0.3em] text-[#C41E3A] mb-4">TEA CULTURE</span>
          <h2 class="font-display text-4xl text-[#1a1a1a] mb-6">The Way of Tea</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 mb-6">
            Tea in China is not merely a beverage — it's a meditative practice, an art form, and a philosophy of life. From the precise movements of Gongfu Cha to the serene simplicity of a single cup, tea embodies the Chinese ideal of harmony.
          </p>
          
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { name: 'Longjing (Dragon Well)', type: 'Green Tea', note: 'Sweet, chestnut aroma', region: 'Hangzhou' },
              { name: 'Tieguanyin', type: 'Oolong Tea', note: 'Floral, orchid notes', region: 'Fujian' },
              { name: 'Dianhong', type: 'Black Tea', note: 'Malty, honey sweetness', region: 'Yunnan' },
              { name: 'Pu-erh', type: 'Fermented Tea', note: 'Earthy, aged complexity', region: 'Yunnan' }
            ].map(tea => (
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4 p-4 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#C41E3A]"></div>
                <div class="flex-1">
                  <span class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a]">{tea.name}</span>
                  <span class="text-stone-400 text-sm ml-2">({tea.type})</span>
                </div>
                <div class="text-right">
                  <div class="text-sm text-stone-600">{tea.note}</div>
                  <div class="text-xs text-[#C41E3A]">{tea.region}</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#C41E3A] to-[#9B1B30]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-white mb-4">Explore More Cuisines</h2>
      <p class="text-red-100 text-lg mb-8">
        Dive deeper into regional specialties, street food culture, and the philosophy of Chinese cooking.
      </p>
      <a href="/" class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-white text-[#C41E3A] font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-stone-100 transition-colors">
        Back to Home
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
